<blockquote>

<P><B><FONT FACE="Arial">Age</FONT>:</B> 66 (July 14, 1931)<BR>
<B><FONT FACE="Arial">Family</FONT>:</B> Married to Mary Gertrude Sudman since 1959. Three children.</P>

<P><IMG SRC="images/Donovan.jpg" WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=264 hspace=6 vspace=4 BORDER=0 align="left" ALT="The Rt. Rev. Herbert A. Donovan"><P>
<B><FONT FACE="Arial">Education</FONT></B>: 
B.A. in economics from the University of Virginia (1954); M.Div. from Virginia Theological Seminary (1957); fellowship, College of Preachers (1976); fellowship, Harvard Divinity School (1987).</P>

<P><B><FONT FACE="Arial">Ministry</FONT></B>: 
Appointed provisional bishop of the Diocese of Chicago January 1998. Assisting bishop, Diocese of New York since 1993. Vicar of Trinity Church, Wall Street, N.Y.C. 1993-1997. Bishop coadjutor of the Diocese of Arkansas 1980-1981. Bishop of the Diocese of Arkansas 1981-1993. Rector of St. Luke's, Montclair, N.J. 1970-1980. Executive officer of the Diocese of Kentucky 1964-1970; canon of Christ Church Cathedral, Louisville 1964-1970. Rector of St. Andrew's, Basin/Greybull, Wy. 1959-1964. Rector of St. John's, Green River, Wy. 1957-1959. Chaplain, U.S. Naval Reserve, rank of captain, 1957-1981. Ordained priest December 1957, Diocese of Wyoming. Ordained deacon June 1957, Diocese of Virginia. </P>

<P><B><FONT FACE="Arial">Appointments</FONT></B>: 
Coordinator, College of Bishops, General Theological Seminary. Trustee, Bard College, Annandale-on-Hudson, New York. Consultant in planned giving, Episcopal Church Foundation. Secretary, House of Bishops (1986-1998). Vice president, Province VII (1984-1990). Executive Council of the Episcopal Church (1979-1980, 1985-1991). Deputy to General Convention (1967-1979).</P>

<P><B><FONT FACE="Arial">Honors\Achievements</FONT></B>: 
D.Div. from Virginia Theological Seminary (1981). D.Div. from University of the South, Sewanee, Tn. (1985). Licensed pilot with multi-engine and instrument ratings.</P>

<P><B><FONT FACE="Arial">Articles</FONT></B>: 
Meditations for Forward Movement Publications. Study guide for the 1973 General Convention.</P>

